'''Sandeggtind Peak''' ({{coord|71|52|S|9|45|E|}})
Peak, 3,055 m, standing 1 mi S of [[Sandho Heights]] on [[Sandegga Ridge]] in the [[Conrad Mountains]], [[Queen Maud Land]]. Discovered and photographed by the [[Third German Antarctic Expedition]] (1938-1939), led by Capt. [[Alfred Ritscher]]. Mapped by Norway from air photos and surveys by NorAE, 1956-60, and named Sandeggtind (sand ridge peak).
